@ThinkingandTinkering Maximum Power Point Tracking refers the the most efficient operating voltage of the solar panel or alternator, measured at the panel or alternator.  On solar panels the brightness of the sun determines that voltage.  On alternators and generators that voltage is determined by the RPM.

An MPPT tries to constantly maintain that ideal voltage at the panel or alternator output  and then converts that voltage to the desired battery charging voltage or inverter input voltage.  Some MPPT controllers can boost the voltage from the panel or alternator if needed for low wind or low sunlight operation.

An MPPT for solar panels will not work for wind turbines.  A true MPPT for wind turbines will have a power curve that needs to be adjusted to match the wind turbine's alternator.  Some high end MPPT controllers can be switched for either wind or solar use, but not both at the same time.
